## Workflow with **ruleprediction-agent** (this inherit doc)

**`sygnif-agent-inherit.mdc`** (this file) and **`.cursor/rules/ruleprediction-agent.mdc`** are used **together** in the worker workflow:

1. **Always-on prediction loop:** `.cursor/rules/sygnif-predict-workflow.mdc` — Predict → Analyze → Proofread → Adjust; horizon check when relevant.
2. **File-scoped prediction / briefing / RAM:** **`.cursor/rules/ruleprediction-agent.mdc`** — same content as the retired name **`ruler-prediction-agent.mdc`**; **`/ruleprediction-agent`** = **`/ruler-prediction-agent`**. It auto-attaches when globs match (`prediction_agent/**`, `scripts/prediction_horizon_check.py`, `finance_agent/http_main.py`, `.cursor/agents/prediction-agent.md`).

When you touch those paths, apply **both** the inherit identity above **and** the **ruleprediction-agent** constraints (single **:8091** listener, no silent live wiring, bounded retrains).

**Continuous rule / data-flow narrative** (optional read for Docker + indicators): **`letscrash/RULE_AND_DATA_FLOW_LOOP.md`** — information → train → propose → prove → test → remove or apply → compare loop; **btc_Trader_Docker** ingress/egress; TradingView / on-chain wishlist.

| Rule | Path | Role |
